SIMPLE: flagrancy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flagrancy
<hw>Fla"gran*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Flagrancies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>flagrantia</ets> a burning. See <er>Flagrant</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A burning; great heat; inflammation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lust causeth a <qex>flagrancy</qex> in the eyes.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The condition or quality of being flagrant;
atrocity; heinousness; enormity; excess.</def>
<rj><au>Steele.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flagrant</ent>⟦br⟧
